{
  "stem": "4284.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "That was just a very strange impression you had.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And you did wonder what those uniforms meant.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "But I had heard about Buchenwald.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "I'd heard about Dachau from people and one distant cousin that had come back in 1939 or actually, early 1940, but I had no idea what this was.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So people were terribly confused.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "People were terribly intimidated because it was only a few minutes later that we realized what this was all about because we were told from the other inmates that this was an extermination camp.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we-- At this point, had you already received a number?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You don't receive a number going in.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I'll tell you in a little bit why, why the number.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So now we realize that the chance of seeing your mother again, whom I only knew with gray hair and when we were so emaciated from the ghetto, to look at this woman and make her appear to be worthy to survive, to be put to forced labor, was basically none.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The concept was that this was a camp where ultimately you were to be exterminated but predominantly, because they were a German industry, to be used for forced labor.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I stayed at camp for about two months.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Nothing.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You just laid around.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The cruelty the Germans exhibited every morning and every night was called appell, which was a head count where you had to stand there.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the Germans would have a great deal of fun hosing you down with water in the cold of the wintertime, making-- having games that one doesn't really want to know about.",
      "word_count": 32
    }
  ],
